description:
**Mobile Developer (Android) - Remote PT**



As an Android Developer, you will create exceptional native experiences with the latest e-commerce tech stack, ensuring a world-class product quality. Our approach to software development is like haute cuisine: every detail is meticulously crafted to deliver a smooth and impactful experience.



You will work with a talented team of Android, iOS, and Quality Assurance engineers who thrive in dynamic and collaborative environments. Additionally, you will contribute to building an app with over 10M+ downloads, featured at the Google I/O 2019 Developer Keynote and multiple case studies. The codebase integrates Arch Components (ViewModel, LiveData, Room, etc.), following a Kotlin-first approach with RxJava & Coroutines and utilizing Agile methodologies such as Scrum and Kanban.



**Requirements:**

**Expertise in:**

-   Kotlin (Kotlin Multiplatform is a plus);
-   Jetpack Compose (Compose Multiplatform is a plus);
-   Coroutines (or RxJava);
-   Software Architecture (MVVM or similar);
-   Unit testing and UI tests;
-   Developing fluid and interactive user experiences;
-   Working independently with a strong sense of responsibility.



**Preferred Skills:**

-   Experience working in cross-functional, feature-oriented teams;
-   Direct collaboration with the client to ensure technical feasibility of requirements;
-   Service-oriented architectures, design patterns, and data structures;
-   Test-driven development and continuous delivery;
-   Monitoring performance metrics and maintaining code quality.



**Key Responsibilities:**

-   Define technical architecture and design;
-   Develop and maintain features in collaboration with the client;
-   Write testable, well-documented code;
-   Ensure the agreed level of test coverage;
-   Take ownership of code from development to maintenance;
-   Mentor junior engineers;
-   Diagnose and solve production issues;
-   Work both autonomously and collaboratively to meet goals;
-   Actively contribute to solution design and implementation.



**Location:**

-   Fully remote, based in Portugal.



If this opportunity excites you, get in touch and join our team!
